audit_report:
 Yes, the smart contract code is vulnerable. The vulnerability lies in the function:

function hashLoop(uint numTimes, bytes32 dataToHash) public returns (bytes32){
for(uint i = 0 ; i < numTimes ; i++){
dataToHash = keccak256(abi.encodePacked(dataToHash));
}
return dataToHash;
}

This function creates a potential for a denial-of-service attack due to the unchecked gas limit in the loop. The gas limit of the transaction containing this function call could be exceeded, causing the contract to become unresponsive.
